Introducing: Camp RunAmock aka The Inner Circle (#116)<br><br>
Come to Camp RunAmock, beat on drums and celebrate manhood and all things manly. Be a brave and mightly keyboard warrior, give your self a brave new name (handle), tell tall tales and preach love for your brother warriors.  No women need apply. Manly men doing manly things. Tell tall tales, drink till you puke, and be brave keyboard soldiers. Be sure and sit around the camp fire and make fun of anyone different than yourself. Sing songs you yourself wrote, preach poetry that you yourself composed, push chapters from a book you yourself wrote, and be sure and attack any other campers who might think differently than you, because are a dog soldier, a mighty warrior, the few, the proud, RunAmonkers.  And here is your theme song, song by the famous choir of Camp RunAmonk, The Village People:<br><br>
&quot;Macho macho man,<br>
I want to be a macho man,<br>
Macho macho man,<br>
I want to be a macho man....<br><br>
Now that you guys have found &quot;your&quot; special place, please do the rest of us a kindness..STAY THERE.
